1
00:00:00,626 --> 00:00:02,503
Why did you meet? What did you talk about?

2
00:00:02,586 --> 00:00:04,046
I found evidence

3
00:00:04,130 --> 00:00:06,549
that the mayor may have been
involved in Sam's death.

4
00:00:06,632 --> 00:00:08,050
Sam is gone, Jackie.

5
00:00:08,134 --> 00:00:10,636
You're just putting our family in danger.

6
00:00:14,807 --> 00:00:16,809
Lieutenant Colonel Cortez!

7
00:00:16,892 --> 00:00:19,895
You're the new police chief of Escondido.

8
00:00:21,397 --> 00:00:22,773
I need someone like you.

9
00:00:22,857 --> 00:00:25,818
Someone who can clean up a mess
even before it spreads.

10
00:00:25,901 --> 00:00:28,070
I'll take responsibility
if you want to keep it.

11
00:00:28,154 --> 00:00:29,822
But that's it. We're through.

12
00:00:29,905 --> 00:00:32,074
Matteo was furious.

13
00:00:32,158 --> 00:00:35,077
He pushed Teacher Sam.

14
00:00:39,790 --> 00:00:41,333
Ma, I'm really sorry.

15
00:01:01,604 --> 00:01:04,440
Matteo, how many times have I told you?

16
00:01:04,523 --> 00:01:06,358
Look at that. You've had too many.

17
00:01:06,442 --> 00:01:07,610
That's enough.

18
00:01:07,693 --> 00:01:09,487
It wasn't me.

19
00:01:10,529 --> 00:01:14,241
Pia ate them all, Papa.

20
00:01:15,117 --> 00:01:18,078
It's in your hand,
and you wouldn't give me any!

21
00:01:20,039 --> 00:01:21,749
Come here.

22
00:01:21,832 --> 00:01:23,042
See? It's empty.

23
00:01:30,758 --> 00:01:32,301
Tell me the truth.

24
00:01:34,220 --> 00:01:36,931
We'll get mad if you break the rules,

25
00:01:37,014 --> 00:01:40,392
but we'll be even madder if you lie.

26
00:01:43,187 --> 00:01:44,647
Come here.

27
00:01:48,150 --> 00:01:49,485
Do you know why?

28
00:01:51,821 --> 00:01:56,367
Because lying is like a stain.

29
00:01:59,286 --> 00:02:03,791
No matter how hard you scrub,

30
00:02:03,874 --> 00:02:05,751
it'll never come off.

31
00:02:05,835 --> 00:02:10,297
And one day,
even if you're telling the truth…

32
00:02:11,924 --> 00:02:14,009
no one will believe you.

33
00:02:20,266 --> 00:02:22,434
Alright. Don't cry anymore.

34
00:02:23,227 --> 00:02:26,272
We just want you to tell the truth.

35
00:02:27,022 --> 00:02:28,315
Always.

36
00:02:30,192 --> 00:02:32,236
Ma, I'm really sorry.

37
00:02:35,531 --> 00:02:37,741
Pa, I'm really sorry.

38
00:02:38,325 --> 00:02:40,703
-I'm really, I--
-What was that?

39
00:02:42,454 --> 00:02:43,497
-What is Jem talking about?
-Hon!

40
00:02:43,581 --> 00:02:44,665
-Explain that!
-Wait!

41
00:02:44,748 --> 00:02:46,208
-Pa, no… I didn't…
-Matteo, what--

42
00:02:46,292 --> 00:02:47,918
-Matteo, what is this?
-Calm down first!

43
00:02:48,002 --> 00:02:49,879
We'll talk about this calmly.

44
00:02:49,962 --> 00:02:52,965
-Pa…
-Go over there first! Now!

45
00:02:55,885 --> 00:02:57,011
Ma…

46
00:02:57,511 --> 00:03:00,514
Let's just talk for a moment. Come on.

47
00:03:00,598 --> 00:03:01,974
Come here.

48
00:03:08,230 --> 00:03:10,399
What's happening?

49
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:20,117
Matteo is in trouble.

50
00:03:24,246 --> 00:03:26,874
I didn't…

51
00:03:34,673 --> 00:03:36,133
It's true.

52
00:03:38,052 --> 00:03:39,929
Jem is pregnant with my child.

53
00:03:44,516 --> 00:03:47,019
I was just scared at first…

54
00:03:48,062 --> 00:03:51,315
because I didn't know how to tell you, Ma.

55
00:03:51,398 --> 00:03:53,484
I don't know what to do.

56
00:03:55,194 --> 00:03:57,780
I was really scared.

57
00:04:02,993 --> 00:04:04,995
But I told her…

58
00:04:06,538 --> 00:04:09,375
I would take responsibility for the baby.

59
00:04:10,834 --> 00:04:14,213
Then, I broke up with her.

60
00:04:14,296 --> 00:04:16,423
You broke up with her
after she got pregnant?

61
00:04:16,507 --> 00:04:19,551
Anton, that's enough!

62
00:04:20,094 --> 00:04:22,304
Stop it!

63
00:04:26,767 --> 00:04:29,019
Matt, when did this start?

64
00:04:29,103 --> 00:04:30,396
When?

65
00:04:31,981 --> 00:04:33,190
And…

66
00:04:34,024 --> 00:04:36,235
what was she saying about Sam?

67
00:04:37,319 --> 00:04:38,570
Ma…

68
00:04:39,571 --> 00:04:41,240
Ma, Pa…

69
00:04:41,991 --> 00:04:43,951
I'm really, really sorry.

70
00:04:44,868 --> 00:04:46,620
I'm really sorry because…

71
00:04:46,704 --> 00:04:49,748
I haven't been honest these past few days.

72
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:53,419
I was just scared…

73
00:04:55,504 --> 00:04:57,464
that I might disappoint you again.

74
00:04:59,842 --> 00:05:02,052
But please, believe me…

75
00:05:04,138 --> 00:05:06,515
I didn't kill Teacher Sam.

76
00:05:07,725 --> 00:05:09,810
Teacher Sam?

77
00:06:17,711 --> 00:06:19,338
What do you think?

78
00:06:20,339 --> 00:06:21,340
Is it good, babe?

79
00:06:25,636 --> 00:06:29,932
Matt was furious.
He wanted to hurt Teacher Sam.

80
00:06:30,015 --> 00:06:33,727
Back at the cliff,
Matt pushed Teacher Sam.

81
00:06:53,163 --> 00:06:57,000
Martinez, I sent you something.
Have you opened it?

82
00:06:57,084 --> 00:06:59,169
Something's going around on the internet.

83
00:06:59,837 --> 00:07:04,174
Looks like we have new suspects
in the Sam Ignacio case.

84
00:07:04,258 --> 00:07:06,510
Go to bed early.

85
00:07:06,593 --> 00:07:08,470
We've got a long day tomorrow.

86
00:07:11,515 --> 00:07:15,060
Please… I didn't kill Teacher Sam.

87
00:07:15,519 --> 00:07:17,688
I could never do that.

88
00:07:18,605 --> 00:07:21,024
-I could never do that.
-What's wrong?

89
00:07:21,525 --> 00:07:26,363
Why are they talking about Teacher Sam?

90
00:07:29,741 --> 00:07:35,706
Matteo would never hurt…

91
00:07:36,957 --> 00:07:40,711
Teacher Sam or anyone.

92
00:07:47,593 --> 00:07:50,387
The day Teacher Sam died…

93
00:07:53,307 --> 00:07:55,559
Jem and I talked.

94
00:07:56,435 --> 00:07:59,229
What did you tell Teacher Sam this time?

95
00:07:59,313 --> 00:08:01,857
Jem, you have no idea
how persistent she is.

96
00:08:01,940 --> 00:08:04,735
You wouldn't answer me.

97
00:08:04,818 --> 00:08:08,197
You wouldn't reply or show up.

98
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:10,324
Who else was I supposed to go to?

99
00:08:10,407 --> 00:08:13,327
I told you I was just waiting
for the right time.

100
00:08:13,410 --> 00:08:14,953
Waiting for what, Matt?

101
00:08:15,621 --> 00:08:18,707
Matt, I'm pregnant.

102
00:08:18,790 --> 00:08:22,586
This isn't some quiz
you can move to next week.

103
00:08:22,669 --> 00:08:26,340
But you didn't have
to tell Teacher Sam everything.

104
00:08:26,423 --> 00:08:28,342
I didn't tell on you.

105
00:08:30,177 --> 00:08:32,095
She's helping me.

106
00:08:32,179 --> 00:08:34,890
Helping? How is that helping?

107
00:08:34,973 --> 00:08:39,102
She keeps bugging me,
pressuring me to tell my parents.

108
00:08:39,186 --> 00:08:42,731
-How is that help? How?
-Matt, she's right.

109
00:08:43,690 --> 00:08:46,068
Matt, I can't do this alone.

110
00:08:50,072 --> 00:08:52,115
I need someone with me.

111
00:08:52,199 --> 00:08:54,326
I need you.

112
00:08:57,454 --> 00:09:02,834
And if you're not here for me or our baby,

113
00:09:04,127 --> 00:09:05,963
at least Teacher Sam is.

114
00:09:06,046 --> 00:09:08,257
There you go again with Teacher Sam.

115
00:09:12,302 --> 00:09:15,180
Where are you? Eli's been waiting for you.

116
00:09:16,431 --> 00:09:18,809
I have to go. I still have to pick up Eli.

117
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:25,232
I picked Eli up from Teacher Sam's place.

118
00:09:25,315 --> 00:09:27,025
Matteo!

119
00:09:28,235 --> 00:09:29,278
Is Jem okay?

120
00:09:32,906 --> 00:09:35,993
I just came to pick up Eli.
Thank you, Teacher Sam.

121
00:09:36,076 --> 00:09:37,035
I'm serious.

122
00:09:37,119 --> 00:09:40,956
If you two don't tell
your parents, I will.

123
00:09:42,124 --> 00:09:43,417
Are we clear?

124
00:09:45,377 --> 00:09:49,047
Then when we got home…

125
00:09:53,885 --> 00:09:55,679
she called me again.

126
00:09:56,513 --> 00:09:58,181
She was crying.

127
00:09:58,724 --> 00:10:00,726
She said she needed me.

128
00:10:02,269 --> 00:10:04,563
So, I went to see her again.

129
00:10:09,276 --> 00:10:10,319
Jem…

130
00:10:18,702 --> 00:10:21,621
You don't have to tell your parents.

131
00:10:22,873 --> 00:10:24,416
What do you mean?

132
00:10:26,084 --> 00:10:28,754
I bought abortion pills online.

133
00:10:32,174 --> 00:10:34,301
What? Jem.

134
00:10:35,260 --> 00:10:36,595
Wait…

135
00:10:39,348 --> 00:10:40,891
What pills?

136
00:10:42,768 --> 00:10:46,563
But, Ma, I didn't force her.

137
00:10:48,857 --> 00:10:51,902
Ma, I didn't force her. I just told her…

138
00:10:51,985 --> 00:10:55,572
if it's dangerous and she's not sure,
then don't go through with it.

139
00:10:58,367 --> 00:11:00,077
I was scared.

140
00:11:01,953 --> 00:11:05,582
I didn't want us fighting about this.

141
00:11:07,459 --> 00:11:11,671
Let's not fight, please.

142
00:11:26,686 --> 00:11:28,939
But I didn't stop her either.

143
00:11:30,732 --> 00:11:33,318
I told her whatever decision she makes,

144
00:11:33,777 --> 00:11:35,529
I'd support her.

145
00:11:35,612 --> 00:11:37,697
That's all. That's all I said.

146
00:11:39,783 --> 00:11:44,371
Then she just cried, and cried,
until she fell asleep.

147
00:11:44,454 --> 00:11:48,667
But she didn't take the pills
while I was there.

148
00:11:52,295 --> 00:11:54,798
After she fell asleep, I went home.

149
00:11:55,507 --> 00:11:56,967
You went straight home?

150
00:11:58,009 --> 00:11:59,010
Yes, Pa.

151
00:11:59,094 --> 00:12:01,847
You didn't go anywhere else?
Didn't talk to anyone?

152
00:12:01,930 --> 00:12:04,182
-Yes. None. I swear.
-Matteo.

153
00:12:04,266 --> 00:12:08,645
Matteo, maybe you're forgetting something.
You have to tell me every little detail!

154
00:12:09,229 --> 00:12:10,272
Anton.

155
00:12:10,355 --> 00:12:12,607
We need to know everything
so we can help Matteo!

156
00:12:12,691 --> 00:12:14,776
I'm telling you everything!

157
00:12:14,860 --> 00:12:18,447
Otherwise, you'll end up in jail!

158
00:12:18,530 --> 00:12:19,865
Pa, I don't want to go to jail.

159
00:12:19,948 --> 00:12:21,992
-Anton, please…
-I don't want to.

160
00:12:22,075 --> 00:12:23,326
-Anton!
-Ma, I can't go to jail.

161
00:12:23,410 --> 00:12:24,911
-Anton, he's scared!
-Will Matteo go to jail?

162
00:12:24,995 --> 00:12:26,746
-You're scaring him!
-He should be!

163
00:12:26,830 --> 00:12:28,331
You should be scared!

164
00:12:28,415 --> 00:12:30,000
Why would you scare him?

165
00:12:31,251 --> 00:12:34,087
Just tell them I did it, Matteo!

166
00:12:34,171 --> 00:12:35,130
No!

167
00:12:35,213 --> 00:12:37,174
-No!
-Stop that! No!

168
00:12:37,257 --> 00:12:39,468
No! That's not happening!

169
00:12:39,551 --> 00:12:40,969
No one's going to jail! No one!

170
00:12:41,052 --> 00:12:43,722
Do you understand? No one's going to jail!

171
00:12:45,932 --> 00:12:46,892
Hey…

172
00:12:49,352 --> 00:12:53,190
Papa's only protecting Matteo.

173
00:12:54,232 --> 00:12:59,905
That's our job. We protect our family.

174
00:13:04,951 --> 00:13:06,036
Pia.

175
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:09,915
Go to Eli's room. Eli, go with her.

176
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:15,337
Stay there, Pia. No one comes out.

177
00:13:19,382 --> 00:13:23,345
-It's crazy if it's true.
-So young.

178
00:13:23,428 --> 00:13:25,138
Poor Jem.

179
00:13:25,222 --> 00:13:27,432
If he's not guilty, why is he being named?

180
00:13:49,663 --> 00:13:51,039
Jem…

181
00:14:05,554 --> 00:14:07,389
She's not answering?

182
00:14:07,472 --> 00:14:09,140
No. Nothing.

183
00:14:14,145 --> 00:14:15,855
What's Jem's number?

184
00:14:15,939 --> 00:14:17,774
Ma, don't. I'll handle it.

185
00:14:17,857 --> 00:14:19,859
-Give it to me.
-I'll call her.

186
00:14:19,943 --> 00:14:20,902
-Jackie.
-Give me her number.

187
00:14:20,986 --> 00:14:22,362
I'll just talk to her.

188
00:14:44,009 --> 00:14:47,846
Jem, it's your Aunt Jackie.

189
00:15:05,530 --> 00:15:06,531
I'm going to see Jem.

190
00:15:06,615 --> 00:15:08,533
Jackie, don't.
It'll just make things worse.

191
00:15:08,617 --> 00:15:09,993
I just want to talk to her.

192
00:15:10,076 --> 00:15:13,121
She shouldn't be scared
if she has nothing to hide.

193
00:15:13,204 --> 00:15:15,248
-I'm coming with you.
-Anton, don't.

194
00:15:15,332 --> 00:15:17,959
Someone has to stay with the kids. Stay.

195
00:15:19,669 --> 00:15:21,504
Ma. Ma…

196
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:58,208
Jem?

197
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:03,505
Jem.

198
00:16:04,923 --> 00:16:08,093
I didn't come here to argue with you.

199
00:16:10,512 --> 00:16:11,930
She's pretty.

200
00:16:13,264 --> 00:16:15,725
Jem, let's talk.

201
00:16:15,809 --> 00:16:17,602
It won't take long.

202
00:16:18,561 --> 00:16:22,190
Jem, if my son did you wrong, I'm here.

203
00:16:22,273 --> 00:16:25,110
Let's talk so I can set
things straight, please.

204
00:16:27,570 --> 00:16:30,115
But if you're only telling lies…

205
00:16:30,198 --> 00:16:32,367
-Who is she?
-please stop it, okay?

206
00:16:32,450 --> 00:16:34,577
Things are getting messy.

207
00:16:41,835 --> 00:16:43,628
Jem, please, let's talk.

208
00:16:43,712 --> 00:16:47,132
Let's fix whatever problem
you and Matteo have.

209
00:16:47,841 --> 00:16:49,300
Let's talk.

210
00:16:49,384 --> 00:16:50,844
That's possible--

211
00:16:50,927 --> 00:16:53,471
Just come back tomorrow.
People are sleeping already.

212
00:16:53,555 --> 00:16:55,890
She obviously doesn't want to talk to you.

213
00:16:55,974 --> 00:16:57,350
Don't force her.

214
00:16:57,434 --> 00:16:59,436
-You're bothering us.
-Is that her?

215
00:16:59,519 --> 00:17:01,271
She's that handsome boy's mother.

216
00:17:01,354 --> 00:17:03,314
You mean the boy who killed his teacher?

217
00:17:03,398 --> 00:17:04,232
Just leave.

218
00:17:04,315 --> 00:17:06,651
The nerve of you to show up here.

219
00:17:06,735 --> 00:17:08,611
Your son is a murderer.

220
00:17:08,695 --> 00:17:10,488
She's got some nerve to come here.

221
00:17:10,572 --> 00:17:12,615
Take a video of her so it'll go viral.

222
00:17:12,699 --> 00:17:15,160
-Yeah, I am.
-She's shameless.

223
00:17:15,243 --> 00:17:16,661
I know, right?

224
00:17:16,745 --> 00:17:19,038
How dare she come here knocking.

225
00:17:46,149 --> 00:17:47,609
How was it? Did you talk to her?

226
00:17:53,823 --> 00:17:55,450
I told you so.

227
00:17:56,326 --> 00:17:59,662
She might come after us
and sue us for harassment.

228
00:17:59,746 --> 00:18:01,414
Then, so be it.

229
00:18:02,207 --> 00:18:03,666
Let her do it.

230
00:18:04,501 --> 00:18:08,421
That way, I can prove that she's lying.

231
00:18:08,505 --> 00:18:13,218
I can't just sit and do nothing,
and wait for Matteo to be arrested.

232
00:18:13,301 --> 00:18:14,719
Tell me.

233
00:18:15,762 --> 00:18:19,557
Are you sure that Matteo
is telling the truth?

234
00:18:20,892 --> 00:18:21,893
Yes.

235
00:18:23,353 --> 00:18:24,979
Because he's my son.

236
00:18:26,523 --> 00:18:28,399
And I know him.

237
00:18:29,192 --> 00:18:30,777
What about you?

238
00:18:30,860 --> 00:18:34,197
Don't you have faith in the child
we raised and disciplined?

239
00:20:41,449 --> 00:20:42,867
Good morning.

240
00:20:43,701 --> 00:20:45,662
Mrs. Carpio, Mr. Carpio.

241
00:20:45,745 --> 00:20:49,791
I'm the lead investigator
in Sam Ignacio's case.

242
00:20:50,333 --> 00:20:53,044
We'd like to talk to Matteo.

243
00:20:54,879 --> 00:20:58,007
It's just a routine interview.
We won't impose anything.

244
00:20:58,841 --> 00:21:02,512
Our son will give a statement,
but not now.

245
00:21:02,595 --> 00:21:04,681
He'll do it at the police station
with a lawyer present.

246
00:21:04,764 --> 00:21:07,976
I understand. We'll wait.

247
00:21:24,659 --> 00:21:25,743
Hello, yes.

248
00:21:25,827 --> 00:21:27,412
I need a lawyer.

249
00:21:27,996 --> 00:21:28,997
Now.

250
00:22:05,450 --> 00:22:06,367
Matt.

251
00:22:06,451 --> 00:22:07,618
There's Jem.

252
00:22:13,833 --> 00:22:14,959
Matt.

253
00:22:15,918 --> 00:22:17,170
Matt.

254
00:22:18,629 --> 00:22:19,505
-Jem.
-Matt.

255
00:22:21,632 --> 00:22:23,301
-Mister, let's go.
-Jem!

256
00:22:23,384 --> 00:22:25,470
-Let's go.
-Jem, let's talk.

257
00:22:25,553 --> 00:22:26,804
Jem! Mister, wait!

258
00:22:26,888 --> 00:22:28,181
-Jem!
-Matt!

259
00:22:28,264 --> 00:22:30,266
-Jem, let's talk!
-Matt!

260
00:22:30,349 --> 00:22:31,517
-Jem!
-Matt!

261
00:22:58,252 --> 00:22:59,587
Good morning.

262
00:23:00,421 --> 00:23:01,297
Paolo Mañego.

263
00:23:01,380 --> 00:23:02,965
Matteo's lawyer.

264
00:23:03,049 --> 00:23:05,843
Chief Cortez isn't here.
He's at the city hall.

265
00:23:05,927 --> 00:23:07,220
He has a meeting with the mayor.

266
00:23:07,303 --> 00:23:08,638
This way, please.

267
00:23:43,714 --> 00:23:45,466
I'll just talk to Jem, okay?

268
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:03,317
Jem.

269
00:24:04,819 --> 00:24:06,028
Can we talk?

270
00:24:06,112 --> 00:24:07,780
Just us two.

271
00:24:07,864 --> 00:24:09,448
I have nothing more to say.

272
00:24:09,532 --> 00:24:11,367
I told the police everything.

273
00:24:12,785 --> 00:24:14,912
You told them the truth?

274
00:24:15,580 --> 00:24:17,415
I don't want to fight.

275
00:24:17,498 --> 00:24:20,835
So do I, Jem.
That's why I want to talk to you.

276
00:24:20,918 --> 00:24:22,545
I don't want any trouble.

277
00:24:23,212 --> 00:24:24,964
Jem, wait.

278
00:24:25,047 --> 00:24:29,969
I know my brother can be stubborn,
but I know that he'd never do that.

279
00:24:30,469 --> 00:24:32,889
Do we really have to reach this point?

280
00:24:33,472 --> 00:24:35,391
Everything I said is true.

281
00:24:35,474 --> 00:24:38,895
Your brother left me on my own
to handle our problems.

282
00:24:40,438 --> 00:24:41,939
I was hurt.

283
00:24:42,023 --> 00:24:45,401
And because of that,
I couldn't control myself.

284
00:24:47,153 --> 00:24:48,196
But, Pia…

285
00:24:49,989 --> 00:24:52,116
This isn't just about me.

286
00:24:52,658 --> 00:24:54,702
I did it for Teacher Sam.

287
00:24:54,785 --> 00:24:57,330
She's the real victim here.

288
00:24:57,997 --> 00:25:00,750
No, Jem. I know my brother.

289
00:25:01,667 --> 00:25:04,420
And I know he'd never do that.

290
00:25:05,004 --> 00:25:06,130
Matteo.

291
00:25:07,673 --> 00:25:09,342
I just want to explain to you

292
00:25:09,425 --> 00:25:12,678
that we reviewed
Jem's livestream confession

293
00:25:12,762 --> 00:25:15,264
and we already got her statement.

294
00:25:17,058 --> 00:25:21,062
You're here so we can hear
your side of the story.

295
00:25:23,397 --> 00:25:25,316
Jem is lying to you.

296
00:25:26,984 --> 00:25:29,445
I won't force you to believe me.

297
00:25:30,404 --> 00:25:31,822
Matteo is your brother.

298
00:25:31,906 --> 00:25:33,824
Of course, you'll take his side.

299
00:25:33,908 --> 00:25:38,162
You'd even cover up for him
when he does something wrong.

300
00:25:41,415 --> 00:25:45,169
But, Pia, do you really know your brother?

301
00:25:46,379 --> 00:25:48,798
If you really know Matteo,

302
00:25:48,881 --> 00:25:53,177
are you sure about where he was
the night Teacher Sam died?

303
00:25:55,846 --> 00:25:59,850
Pia, Matteo killed Teacher Sam!

304
00:26:02,520 --> 00:26:03,896
So that's it.

305
00:26:04,522 --> 00:26:06,524
She told me that she took care of it.

306
00:26:06,607 --> 00:26:08,401
That our problem is gone.

307
00:26:10,903 --> 00:26:12,446
She said…

308
00:26:16,033 --> 00:26:17,493
the baby is gone.

309
00:26:19,704 --> 00:26:21,789
She had the baby aborted.

310
00:26:25,501 --> 00:26:30,298
But a few days after telling me that…

311
00:26:31,590 --> 00:26:34,760
she confessed to me that she lied.

312
00:26:38,973 --> 00:26:41,600
She said she's still pregnant.

313
00:26:43,519 --> 00:26:45,688
She told me she couldn't bear…

314
00:26:49,817 --> 00:26:52,111
She couldn't bear
to have the baby aborted.

315
00:26:54,447 --> 00:26:56,907
She said she couldn't hurt the baby.

316
00:26:57,491 --> 00:26:59,076
See?

317
00:26:59,160 --> 00:27:00,494
She's a liar, right?

318
00:27:04,540 --> 00:27:08,878
The night you went to
Jem's house and the night…

319
00:27:09,754 --> 00:27:11,630
Teacher Sam fell off the cliff…

320
00:27:14,508 --> 00:27:17,636
You knew that Jem
was still pregnant, right?

321
00:27:20,514 --> 00:27:21,474
Yes.

322
00:27:21,557 --> 00:27:23,809
Did you get mad at her

323
00:27:23,893 --> 00:27:26,645
because she told Teacher Sam
she was pregnant?

324
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:29,482
Were you mad at Teacher Sam?

325
00:27:32,777 --> 00:27:33,819
No!

326
00:27:35,821 --> 00:27:36,906
That's not true.

327
00:27:36,989 --> 00:27:39,575
Matteo wanted to break up
with you because you're a liar.

328
00:27:39,658 --> 00:27:41,702
You're just fooling him!

329
00:27:41,786 --> 00:27:44,372
You're fooling him so he won't leave you!

330
00:27:44,455 --> 00:27:47,958
-There's a reason why I did that.
-Yes, you have a reason!

331
00:27:48,042 --> 00:27:50,211
You want to get back at him

332
00:27:50,294 --> 00:27:52,463
because he no longer wants to be with you!

333
00:27:55,007 --> 00:27:56,967
You don't have to answer
if you don't want to.

334
00:28:13,442 --> 00:28:15,945
Ma'am, all I want is that,

335
00:28:16,028 --> 00:28:18,823
if my parents find out…

336
00:28:20,616 --> 00:28:22,576
I want it to come from me.

337
00:28:24,829 --> 00:28:26,956
Not from Teacher Sam.

338
00:28:27,998 --> 00:28:30,459
But she kept pressuring me.

339
00:28:31,836 --> 00:28:33,796
I didn't know what to do.

340
00:28:41,512 --> 00:28:44,640
I agreed to talk to you,
but don't insult me.

341
00:28:44,723 --> 00:28:47,601
If you're just going to insult me,
then leave!

342
00:28:47,685 --> 00:28:50,646
Go be with your murderer brother!

343
00:28:50,729 --> 00:28:53,065
He might not come home anymore!

344
00:28:54,608 --> 00:28:55,901
You liar!

345
00:28:55,985 --> 00:28:58,529
-Ow!
-Damn you!

346
00:28:58,612 --> 00:29:00,531
Ouch! Let go of me!

347
00:29:00,614 --> 00:29:03,033
-That hurts!
-You're a liar!

348
00:29:03,117 --> 00:29:03,951
Ow!

349
00:29:04,827 --> 00:29:07,037
Damn you!

350
00:29:08,330 --> 00:29:10,291
Jem!

351
00:29:10,374 --> 00:29:13,627
Eli! Eli…

352
00:29:13,711 --> 00:29:15,129
Eli, Eli!

353
00:29:15,212 --> 00:29:17,548
Hey! What's going on here?

354
00:29:18,841 --> 00:29:21,385
Call the nurse! Hurry!

355
00:29:22,178 --> 00:29:23,762
Jem's baby!

356
00:29:23,846 --> 00:29:25,347
Dear, are you okay?

357
00:29:32,813 --> 00:29:36,942
Let's go back to the night
you went to Jem's house.

358
00:29:38,444 --> 00:29:41,447
Do you remember
what time Matteo came home?

359
00:29:45,409 --> 00:29:47,620
We went to bed earlier than usual

360
00:29:47,703 --> 00:29:50,581
to attend the school's
Family Day the next morning.

361
00:29:51,582 --> 00:29:55,503
So, you don't know
what time your son came home.

362
00:29:55,586 --> 00:29:58,255
Or did you not know that he left?

363
00:29:58,339 --> 00:29:59,798
No…

364
00:29:59,882 --> 00:30:01,509
You see, ma'am…

365
00:30:02,051 --> 00:30:04,762
It was already late when I came home.

366
00:30:05,471 --> 00:30:07,890
Everyone in the house was asleep.

367
00:30:25,658 --> 00:30:26,867
At school?

368
00:30:28,327 --> 00:30:29,703
What?

369
00:30:29,787 --> 00:30:33,040
You go ahead. I'll be there in a bit.

370
00:30:33,123 --> 00:30:35,000
You handle things there. Thank you.

371
00:30:38,754 --> 00:30:41,799
Jem is in the hospital.
Something happened to her.

372
00:30:41,882 --> 00:30:43,926
Eli and Pia are there too.

373
00:30:44,009 --> 00:30:45,553
I'll go to them.

374
00:30:45,636 --> 00:30:47,596
I'll leave you here with Matteo, okay?

375
00:30:49,098 --> 00:30:50,266
-Ma.
-Matt.

376
00:30:53,143 --> 00:30:54,353
I'll go now.

377
00:31:10,744 --> 00:31:11,870
Are you okay?

378
00:31:39,023 --> 00:31:42,109
Pia, your mom's on her way.

379
00:31:51,535 --> 00:31:53,287
-Pia.
-Ma.

380
00:31:56,582 --> 00:31:58,083
I'm here now.

381
00:31:58,917 --> 00:32:03,130
I'm sorry, Ma. I'm sorry.

382
00:32:07,885 --> 00:32:09,595
I'm so sorry.

383
00:32:15,267 --> 00:32:18,729
I'm here now. Stop crying.

384
00:32:19,271 --> 00:32:20,648
There, there.

385
00:32:53,597 --> 00:32:56,558
Doc, we're Jem's teachers at school.

386
00:32:56,642 --> 00:32:58,977
We've called her legal guardian.

387
00:32:59,061 --> 00:33:01,730
But for now,
can you tell us about her condition?

388
00:33:06,652 --> 00:33:08,904
There's a small laceration on the leg.

389
00:33:09,488 --> 00:33:12,491
It's nothing serious,
but we gave her an anti-tetanus shot.

390
00:33:15,619 --> 00:33:19,790
The school nurse mentioned
the patient might be pregnant.

391
00:33:19,873 --> 00:33:21,041
So, we checked.

392
00:33:21,750 --> 00:33:24,461
So is Jem's baby okay?

393
00:33:30,467 --> 00:33:32,052
But she said…

394
00:33:39,309 --> 00:33:40,978
What's that, Doc?

395
00:33:55,576 --> 00:33:57,286
So, she's not pregnant?

396
00:34:14,636 --> 00:34:16,305
Thank you, Doc.

397
00:34:53,634 --> 00:34:54,802
Jackie?

398
00:34:56,136 --> 00:34:57,679
Jem has confessed.

399
00:34:58,764 --> 00:35:00,265
She lied.

400
00:35:01,266 --> 00:35:03,435
We can take Matteo home.

401
00:35:13,153 --> 00:35:14,738
Let's go.

402
00:35:47,437 --> 00:35:49,439
We can go home now, Matt.

403
00:35:49,523 --> 00:35:51,525
We can go home now.

404
00:35:55,153 --> 00:35:56,280
What?

405
00:35:56,905 --> 00:36:00,409
Go see Jem Garcia at the hospital.

406
00:36:00,492 --> 00:36:02,661
Find out what's going on in there.

407
00:36:28,145 --> 00:36:31,231
Jem Garcia has withdrawn her statement.

408
00:36:31,315 --> 00:36:33,692
Thank you for your cooperation.

409
00:36:33,775 --> 00:36:35,068
Thank you.

410
00:36:44,369 --> 00:36:46,371
Bro, thank you.

411
00:36:54,546 --> 00:36:55,380
Matt.

412
00:36:56,089 --> 00:36:57,090
Thank you.

413
00:38:16,712 --> 00:38:18,672
I can't hide it anymore.

414
00:38:19,923 --> 00:38:22,050
My conscience is eating me alive.

415
00:38:23,593 --> 00:38:26,847
My sister keeps appearing
in my dreams every night.

416
00:38:27,889 --> 00:38:29,433
The truth is…

417
00:38:30,392 --> 00:38:33,145
she was good to me.

418
00:38:33,895 --> 00:38:36,648
She tried to help me many times.

419
00:38:37,733 --> 00:38:39,234
But until the very end,

420
00:38:40,360 --> 00:38:44,364
I never managed to do
anything right for her.

421
00:38:46,700 --> 00:38:48,618
I'll admit it now.

422
00:38:50,746 --> 00:38:52,539
I'm the one who killed Sam.

423
00:38:53,749 --> 00:38:55,459
I'm the one who killed my sister.

424
00:39:05,927 --> 00:39:07,721
I didn't want to lose you.

425
00:39:17,397 --> 00:39:19,900
As tragic as this incident is,

426
00:39:19,983 --> 00:39:23,862
I can say that today is a victory

427
00:39:23,945 --> 00:39:25,906
for everyone who loved Sam.

428
00:39:27,324 --> 00:39:30,160
Her case has finally been solved

429
00:39:31,078 --> 00:39:34,790
so her soul can finally rest in peace.

430
00:39:35,540 --> 00:39:38,085
That's what I promised you, right?

431
00:39:38,168 --> 00:39:40,420
That the truth would come out.

432
00:40:29,553 --> 00:40:34,558
I thought we were going to lose him.

433
00:40:38,937 --> 00:40:41,273
One false story…

434
00:40:42,190 --> 00:40:44,693
One fake post…

435
00:40:47,779 --> 00:40:51,408
And you can lose your child.

436
00:41:02,169 --> 00:41:05,172
Something was taken from our son.

437
00:41:05,797 --> 00:41:09,551
Something was taken from our family
that we can never get back.

438
00:41:19,102 --> 00:41:21,229
We got him back.

439
00:41:22,063 --> 00:41:23,773
That's what matters.

440
00:41:24,983 --> 00:41:26,443
And eventually,

441
00:41:27,986 --> 00:41:30,197
Matteo will be okay too.

442
00:42:07,817 --> 00:42:10,403
Anton, stop!

443
00:42:21,414 --> 00:42:22,999
We can't.

444
00:42:27,295 --> 00:42:29,089
We can no longer go back
to the way we were before.

445
00:43:14,134 --> 00:43:19,597
How about you, Anton?
When are you going to confess?

446
00:43:21,766 --> 00:43:23,643
I've said everything I needed to say.

447
00:43:23,727 --> 00:43:24,936
I know you're hiding something.

448
00:43:25,020 --> 00:43:26,563
There's nothing I can do
if you don't want to believe me.

449
00:43:26,646 --> 00:43:27,897
Who are you taking the fall for?

450
00:43:27,981 --> 00:43:30,358
I'm sure this case has kept you up
for nights on end.

451
00:43:30,442 --> 00:43:33,153
So let's not make things
harder for ourselves.

452
00:43:33,236 --> 00:43:37,157
Some things are better left closed.

453
00:43:37,240 --> 00:43:39,242
Sam Ignacio's case isn't closed yet.

454
00:43:39,326 --> 00:43:42,203
I want to find evidence,
so I'm just playing along for now.

455
00:43:42,287 --> 00:43:43,538
If there's corruption,

456
00:43:43,621 --> 00:43:46,374
isn't it even more dangerous
to just look the other way?

457
00:43:46,458 --> 00:43:49,461
I'm not reckless,
but I won't back down either.

458
00:43:49,544 --> 00:43:52,130
-How far will you go?
-Until the truth comes out.

459
00:43:52,213 --> 00:43:55,258
Until everything's clear for our kids.

460
00:43:55,342 --> 00:43:57,802
I won't put our family in danger.

461
00:43:57,886 --> 00:44:01,348
But I also won't let fear
dictate our choices.
